1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:32,280 --> 00:01:40,640
[You are My Fateful Love]
[EP23]

3
00:01:58,799 --> 00:02:00,159
If the Poet didn't get hand on

4
00:02:00,159 --> 00:02:01,120
those specific details,

5
00:02:02,519 --> 00:02:04,280
he could never have the exact same ideas as mine.

6
00:02:10,919 --> 00:02:11,479
Mingying.

7
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:12,919
Did you save these details

8
00:02:12,919 --> 00:02:14,159
anywhere else?

9
00:02:14,479 --> 00:02:15,319
Besides the USB drive,

10
00:02:15,319 --> 00:02:16,560
it's only on my computer.

11
00:02:18,319 --> 00:02:19,000
Could it be...

12
00:02:20,199 --> 00:02:21,840
My computer was hacked?

13
00:02:22,800 --> 00:02:25,199
Who would hack your computer?

14
00:02:28,680 --> 00:02:29,680
Cen Sisi.

15
00:02:34,120 --> 00:02:34,719
Shican.

16
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:36,840
This new song you wrote in Shen'ao

17
00:02:36,840 --> 00:02:37,719
is getting good feedback.

18
00:02:38,520 --> 00:02:39,599
It is a nice payday.

19
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:42,560
Shican's talent is beyond question.

20
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:45,240
Talent needs promotion too.

21
00:02:46,520 --> 00:02:47,719
Shican, you know

22
00:02:48,120 --> 00:02:49,039
hype...

23
00:02:49,039 --> 00:02:50,400
you can't rely on personal ability alone.

24
00:02:51,240 --> 00:02:52,039
This single of yours

25
00:02:52,039 --> 00:02:53,719
achieved this result

26
00:02:53,879 --> 00:02:55,319
because the company put in a lot of effort.

27
00:02:56,319 --> 00:02:58,000
I thank everyone for hard work.

28
00:02:59,520 --> 00:03:00,680
As long as you know.

29
00:03:00,919 --> 00:03:01,960
So you must not let

30
00:03:01,960 --> 00:03:02,960
everyone's hard work on you go to waste.

31
00:03:03,240 --> 00:03:04,439
Even though you have hype now,

32
00:03:04,439 --> 00:03:05,800
you still need to go to events,

33
00:03:05,800 --> 00:03:06,879
take the endorsements.

34
00:03:07,439 --> 00:03:08,199
Don't be picky.

35
00:03:08,199 --> 00:03:09,280
Fans will buy anything anyway.

36
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:14,759
You're right.

37
00:03:15,680 --> 00:03:17,439
But looking at these recent endorsement

38
00:03:17,879 --> 00:03:18,599
offers,

39
00:03:19,120 --> 00:03:19,800
they're pretty thin.

40
00:03:21,639 --> 00:03:22,439
You call that thin?

41
00:03:24,199 --> 00:03:24,719
Bro,

42
00:03:25,319 --> 00:03:26,680
our hype has increased lately,

43
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:27,960
so the value has gone up.

44
00:03:28,599 --> 00:03:30,400
During this time, we should strike while the iron is hot

45
00:03:30,479 --> 00:03:31,319
and make a new album.

46
00:03:32,080 --> 00:03:33,080
Then the endorsements we get

47
00:03:33,319 --> 00:03:34,560
won't be at this level anymore.

48
00:03:37,240 --> 00:03:37,599
So,

49
00:03:37,599 --> 00:03:38,759
you have ideas for a new album?

50
00:03:39,599 --> 00:03:40,800
I've been having a lot of inspiration lately.

51
00:03:41,039 --> 00:03:41,919
Making a mini album
won't take long.

52
00:03:45,919 --> 00:03:46,639
Alright.

53
00:03:47,319 --> 00:03:49,199
Looks like that trip to Shen'ao was worthwhile.

54
00:03:49,199 --> 00:03:49,960
You've wised up.

55
00:03:50,719 --> 00:03:51,560
Then hurry and prepare
your new album.

56
00:03:52,280 --> 00:03:53,520
I'll postpone these endorsements.

57
00:03:53,919 --> 00:03:54,879
Take good care of Shican.

58
00:03:58,520 --> 00:03:59,280
Shican.

59
00:04:00,919 --> 00:04:01,919
What are you...

60
00:04:09,599 --> 00:04:10,159
[Shican.]

61
00:04:10,280 --> 00:04:11,800
[Are you free to talk on the phone right now?]

62
00:04:13,960 --> 00:04:15,039
Hacking the computer?

63
00:04:16,199 --> 00:04:17,319
That shouldn't be possible.

64
00:04:17,680 --> 00:04:18,800
Then it's really strange.

65
00:04:19,199 --> 00:04:20,560
Cen Sisi is still getting treatment abroad,

66
00:04:20,879 --> 00:04:22,079
she's been doing much better lately.

67
00:04:22,399 --> 00:04:23,079
I'll ask her for you

68
00:04:23,319 --> 00:04:24,160
if anything like that happened.

69
00:04:24,399 --> 00:04:25,920
Okay, thank you, Shican.

70
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:28,279
No trouble.

71
00:04:30,399 --> 00:04:31,519
Asking about this...

72
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:33,839
Did something happen?

73
00:04:34,519 --> 00:04:35,160
Xu Huaisong
didn't help you handle it?

74
00:04:37,279 --> 00:04:38,199
Nothing happened.

75
00:04:39,040 --> 00:04:39,839
He...

76
00:04:41,040 --> 00:04:42,399
He's been busy abroad lately,

77
00:04:42,879 --> 00:04:44,000
so I won't bother him.

78
00:04:47,240 --> 00:04:48,399
I'll let you go too.

79
00:04:48,839 --> 00:04:50,240
Congratulations on your successful single release.

80
00:04:50,519 --> 00:04:51,279
You go ahead.

81
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:54,360
Okay.

82
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:08,800
[On your way back from shopping,]

83
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:09,759
[bring some fruit.]

84
00:05:09,839 --> 00:05:11,680
[Zhou Jun finished his project]

85
00:05:11,879 --> 00:05:12,879
[and insisted on coming to thank me in person.]

86
00:05:12,879 --> 00:05:14,000
[He said since tomorrow is the weekend,]

87
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:15,279
[he'll bring his girlfriend.]

88
00:05:15,360 --> 00:05:15,959
[This kid]

89
00:05:16,199 --> 00:05:17,199
[is so polite.]

90
00:05:17,439 --> 00:05:18,399
[Then tomorrow, we'll take the two kids]
[to that nearby farmhouse restaurant]

91
00:05:19,399 --> 00:05:20,120
[for a meal.]

92
00:05:20,519 --> 00:05:21,199
[Yesterday you said the novel,]
[you've finished writing it.]

93
00:05:22,360 --> 00:05:23,040
[So you have time]
[to come back for a visit?]

94
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:25,279
[We'll treat you too.]

95
00:05:28,519 --> 00:05:30,000
[So I'm just an afterthought, huh?]

96
00:05:41,920 --> 00:05:43,360
After the suspect was released,

97
00:05:43,360 --> 00:05:45,000
things got even worse.

98
00:05:45,759 --> 00:05:47,720
Neighbors gossip about our family.

99
00:05:48,399 --> 00:05:49,360
The victim's family

100
00:05:49,360 --> 00:05:51,000
comes to harass us every few days,

101
00:05:51,639 --> 00:05:53,399
throwing paint, smashing eggs.

102
00:05:54,319 --> 00:05:55,560
They also say my father

103
00:05:56,680 --> 00:05:58,279
is an accomplice to a murderer.

104
00:05:59,199 --> 00:06:00,519
What case is this?

105
00:06:02,199 --> 00:06:03,600
How come I've never heard of it.

106
00:06:53,399 --> 00:06:54,839
Still reading so late.

107
00:06:56,319 --> 00:06:56,800
Oh, right.

108
00:06:57,040 --> 00:06:58,480
The doctor said Mr. Xu's condition

109
00:06:58,480 --> 00:06:59,199
has stabilized,

110
00:06:59,199 --> 00:07:00,319
and he can be discharged in a couple of days.

111
00:07:00,519 --> 00:07:01,959
If you're busy, you can head back first.

112
00:07:01,959 --> 00:07:02,800
I'll keep an eye on things here.

113
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:03,800
It's okay.

114
00:07:04,120 --> 00:07:05,040
It's only a couple more days.

115
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:07,959
I see you've been
reading this book lately.

116
00:07:08,920 --> 00:07:09,519
It is...

117
00:07:11,680 --> 00:07:12,360
I'm preparing

118
00:07:12,360 --> 00:07:13,439
for the national judicial exam.

119
00:07:14,480 --> 00:07:15,680
Alright, then you go ahead.

120
00:07:15,720 --> 00:07:16,439
I won't disturb you.
I'll go to the bathroom.

121
00:07:17,399 --> 00:07:18,560
Okay, thanks.

122
00:07:18,879 --> 00:07:19,399
No problem.

123
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:32,720
[Sis, just letting you know,]

124
00:07:32,720 --> 00:07:33,720
[I'm home.]

125
00:07:41,879 --> 00:07:42,519
[Okay.]

126
00:07:42,839 --> 00:07:44,360
[Don't worry about your brother and me.]

127
00:07:44,720 --> 00:07:45,920
[We'll sort it out ourselves.]

128
00:07:46,279 --> 00:07:47,240
[Focus on your studies.]

129
00:08:07,759 --> 00:08:09,040
Actually, your brother and I

130
00:08:10,079 --> 00:08:11,519
have only really known each other

131
00:08:12,360 --> 00:08:13,560
for a little over half a year.

132
00:08:15,720 --> 00:08:16,439
What's wrong?

133
00:08:16,720 --> 00:08:17,680
The USB drive I used to save the outline
isn't lost.

134
00:08:20,079 --> 00:08:20,959
Then how did the Poet

135
00:08:22,040 --> 00:08:23,720
get my ideas?

136
00:08:28,639 --> 00:08:29,120
Why didn't I

137
00:08:29,120 --> 00:08:30,759
just say that earlier.

138
00:08:35,919 --> 00:08:36,639
No, no.

139
00:09:03,879 --> 00:09:04,720
Strange.

140
00:09:05,440 --> 00:09:05,960
Why are both

141
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:07,000
not answering.

142
00:09:10,879 --> 00:09:11,480
Mom.

143
00:09:11,759 --> 00:09:12,840
I haven't rested well these days.

144
00:09:12,840 --> 00:09:14,000
and overslept a bit today.

145
00:09:14,639 --> 00:09:15,759
I'm heading out now.

146
00:09:15,799 --> 00:09:17,120
If I'm late,

147
00:09:17,440 --> 00:09:18,320
you and dad can eat first.
Don't wait for me.

148
00:09:23,759 --> 00:09:24,279
Hello.

149
00:09:24,519 --> 00:09:26,639
[Hello, is this Ms. Ruan?]

150
00:09:26,639 --> 00:09:27,240
Speaking.

151
00:09:27,879 --> 00:09:28,480
[Ms. Ruan,]

152
00:09:29,240 --> 00:09:31,240
[this is Fang Zhen from the Hang City Public Security Bureau.]

153
00:09:31,720 --> 00:09:32,639
[Your father...]

154
00:09:45,320 --> 00:09:46,399
Hello, Huai... Huaisong?

155
00:09:46,519 --> 00:09:47,679
Hello, Ruan Yu.

156
00:09:47,919 --> 00:09:48,960
What exactly is happening?

157
00:09:50,600 --> 00:09:51,480
I... I don't know

158
00:09:51,480 --> 00:09:52,559
what exactly is happening.

159
00:09:53,720 --> 00:09:54,840
To... today,

160
00:09:55,320 --> 00:09:56,399
Zhou Jun was supposed to bring Yao Xin

161
00:09:56,480 --> 00:09:57,600
to my parents' home for dinner.

162
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:58,960
But for some reason,

163
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:01,159
Zhou Jun came alone.

164
00:10:01,480 --> 00:10:02,159
And then...

165
00:10:03,480 --> 00:10:04,360
I... I don't know
what happened,

166
00:10:05,279 --> 00:10:06,919
and the police came looking for Zhou Jun.

167
00:10:07,360 --> 00:10:08,000
Zhou Jun didn't want

168
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:09,039
to go with them.

169
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:10,399
He... in his panic,

170
00:10:10,399 --> 00:10:11,720
he... he took my father hostage.

171
00:10:13,759 --> 00:10:14,720
The p... police just told me
that much.

172
00:10:15,480 --> 00:10:16,600
Are you safe now?

173
00:10:16,600 --> 00:10:17,480
Where are you?

174
00:10:17,879 --> 00:10:18,759
I'm in a police car.

175
00:10:19,120 --> 00:10:20,320
I'm on my way there now.

176
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:22,039
The way to there...

177
00:10:26,360 --> 00:10:27,000
Ruan Yu.

178
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:28,759
Don't be scared.

179
00:10:29,120 --> 00:10:30,600
Calm down and listen carefully to me.

180
00:10:31,120 --> 00:10:31,759
Okay.

181
00:10:32,080 --> 00:10:33,120
In this kind of situation,

182
00:10:33,120 --> 00:10:34,799
SWAT, firefighters, and medical personnel

183
00:10:34,799 --> 00:10:36,039
will definitely be on the scene

184
00:10:36,039 --> 00:10:37,039
immediately.

185
00:10:37,320 --> 00:10:37,960
Our country's

186
00:10:37,960 --> 00:10:39,440
hostage rescue success rate

187
00:10:39,440 --> 00:10:40,279
is very high.

188
00:10:40,679 --> 00:10:41,879
The police's principle is always

189
00:10:41,879 --> 00:10:43,279
to prioritize the hostage's

190
00:10:43,279 --> 00:10:44,039
life safety.

191
00:10:44,840 --> 00:10:45,679
The worst-case scenario

192
00:10:46,080 --> 00:10:47,279
is, in an emergency,

193
00:10:47,279 --> 00:10:47,799
to ensure

194
00:10:47,799 --> 00:10:49,240
the hostage's safety

195
00:10:49,879 --> 00:10:50,919
by neutralizing the captor.

196
00:10:52,039 --> 00:10:52,799
So regardless of why Zhou Jun

197
00:10:52,799 --> 00:10:54,480
took the teacher hostage,

198
00:10:54,879 --> 00:10:55,840
trust the police,

199
00:10:56,200 --> 00:10:57,039
cooperate with them.

200
00:10:57,519 --> 00:10:58,559
The teacher will be fine.

201
00:10:59,919 --> 00:11:00,639
Okay.

202
00:11:01,279 --> 00:11:02,039
I know.

203
00:11:03,120 --> 00:11:03,840
I know.

204
00:11:04,039 --> 00:11:04,919
Let me know

205
00:11:05,279 --> 00:11:06,120
immediately if anything happens.

206
00:11:10,679 --> 00:11:11,639
Don't come closer!

207
00:11:12,639 --> 00:11:13,559
Don't push me!

208
00:11:14,519 --> 00:11:16,440
Step back! I said step back!

209
00:11:23,679 --> 00:11:25,799
All of you get down! Get down!

210
00:11:27,440 --> 00:11:28,039
Mom.

211
00:11:28,639 --> 00:11:30,240
Yu, you're here.

212
00:11:30,320 --> 00:11:31,320
Look at your father.

213
00:11:31,679 --> 00:11:33,000
I told you not to come closer!

214
00:11:33,480 --> 00:11:35,360
Mom, what exactly is going on?

215
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:36,000
I...

216
00:11:37,279 --> 00:11:38,600
I can't explain clearly.

217
00:11:39,519 --> 00:11:40,759
When he came, he said he

218
00:11:40,759 --> 00:11:41,799
was in a bad mood.

219
00:11:41,879 --> 00:11:43,279
Seems like he argued with his girlfriend.

220
00:11:43,440 --> 00:11:44,159
Then your father and I

221
00:11:44,159 --> 00:11:45,279
tried to comfort him for a long time.

222
00:11:45,600 --> 00:11:46,600
Everything was fine then...

223
00:11:46,960 --> 00:11:47,960
It was fine.

224
00:11:48,960 --> 00:11:49,919
Mom, don't cry.

225
00:11:50,320 --> 00:11:50,960
It's okay.

226
00:11:51,279 --> 00:11:52,080
Later, his phone
was run out of battery.

227
00:11:52,840 --> 00:11:53,799
He... he plugged it in

228
00:11:53,799 --> 00:11:54,840
to charge and turned it on.

229
00:11:54,840 --> 00:11:56,120
As soon as he looked, he said something about trouble,

230
00:11:56,120 --> 00:11:56,720
and rushed out.

231
00:11:56,720 --> 00:11:58,000
Then the police... the...

232
00:11:58,000 --> 00:11:59,279
The police arrived.

233
00:11:59,960 --> 00:12:01,799
Okay, Mom, don't... don't be scared.

234
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:03,440
The police will handle it.

235
00:12:03,759 --> 00:12:04,600
They'll figure it out.

236
00:12:05,320 --> 00:12:06,120
Officer,

237
00:12:06,639 --> 00:12:07,240
what exactly
did this kid do?

238
00:12:08,120 --> 00:12:09,320
He's usually such a good kid.

239
00:12:09,320 --> 00:12:10,080
What happened to him?

240
00:12:10,399 --> 00:12:11,600
Mrs. Ruan, we can't disclose

241
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:12,519
specific case details for now.
Captain Fang.

242
00:12:13,600 --> 00:12:15,000
The suspect's emotions

243
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:15,879
is very volatile.

244
00:12:16,080 --> 00:12:16,840
He's very resistant
to our negotiations.

245
00:12:17,720 --> 00:12:19,200
Should we use forceful measures?

246
00:12:20,080 --> 00:12:20,879
Observe a bit longer.

247
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:23,120
Um, Officer,

248
00:12:23,279 --> 00:12:24,840
this forceful measure you mentioned,

249
00:12:24,840 --> 00:12:26,000
is it aimed at Zhou Jun?

250
00:12:29,919 --> 00:12:30,720
Officer,

251
00:12:31,320 --> 00:12:32,559
could I go up and try to talk to him?

252
00:12:33,039 --> 00:12:33,879
You can't go.
It's so dangerous up there.

253
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:36,000
You can't go. Mom...

254
00:12:36,120 --> 00:12:37,279
Calm down, listen to me.

255
00:12:37,720 --> 00:12:38,879
Zhou Jun and I were close

256
00:12:38,879 --> 00:12:39,840
in high school.

257
00:12:40,200 --> 00:12:40,879
I've also met him
a few times recently.

258
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:42,840
If I go up,
maybe he won't be as

259
00:12:43,799 --> 00:12:44,559
defensive.

260
00:12:44,799 --> 00:12:45,679
I might be able

261
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:47,120
to calm him down.

262
00:12:47,919 --> 00:12:48,480
Well...

263
00:12:50,360 --> 00:12:51,799
Go get a concealed earpiece

264
00:12:51,799 --> 00:12:52,519
for Ms. Ruan.

265
00:12:53,080 --> 00:12:53,639
Okay.

266
00:12:54,360 --> 00:12:55,279
We'll maintain communication
with you through the earpiece,

267
00:12:56,279 --> 00:12:56,679
and tell you

268
00:12:56,679 --> 00:12:58,039
hat to say to the suspect.

269
00:12:58,440 --> 00:12:59,919
Remember, do what you can.

270
00:13:00,200 --> 00:13:01,159
The police are right behind you.

271
00:13:01,720 --> 00:13:02,000
Okay.

272
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:03,200
If anything happens,

273
00:13:03,200 --> 00:13:04,159
retreat immediately.

274
00:13:04,639 --> 00:13:05,440
We have other means

275
00:13:05,440 --> 00:13:06,600
to ensure your and your father's safety.

276
00:13:06,720 --> 00:13:07,120
Okay.
Don't worry, Mrs. Qu.

277
00:13:08,559 --> 00:13:09,320
Cui, be careful.
Listen to the officer.

278
00:13:10,080 --> 00:13:10,840
Take care of yourself.
Don't be scared, Mom.

279
00:13:11,399 --> 00:13:12,440
Be careful, Yu.

280
00:13:12,519 --> 00:13:13,279
Watch out.
This way.

281
00:13:16,919 --> 00:13:18,039
Don't worry, Mrs. Qu.

282
00:13:23,720 --> 00:13:25,480
Don't come up! No one come up!

283
00:13:25,639 --> 00:13:27,000
I said don't let anyone up!

284
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:27,919
Zhou Jun, it's me.

285
00:13:28,799 --> 00:13:29,480
